message: /* Arguments */ The deletion of my section was not necessary. I have no problem with constructive criticism. I am not a stubborn individual & I am can be reasoned with. I am open to & I encourage civilized conflict. There is no need for fighting. We are grown adults.

I slightly changed the definition. It originally states that antinatalism is the view that procreation is bad and immoral. The words, "bad" &, "immoral" are synonymous. There is no need to say that something is bad but that it's also immoral. It's like saying, you are ill but that you are also sick.
/* What is your problem? */ new section
Omnicide also refers to the destruction of non human life as described in the Mariam Webster dictionary. Not just human life.
